# Sūra XXVI.: Shu‘arāa, or The Poets.

### Section 3

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_034.gif)

34. Q<u>a</u>la lilmala-i <u>h</u>awlahu inna h<u>atha</u>
las<u>ah</u>irun AAaleem**un**

34\. (Pharaoh) said to the Chiefs  
Around him: "This is indeed  
A sorcerer well-versed:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_035.gif)

35. Yureedu an yukhrijakum min ar<u>d</u>ikum bisi<u>h</u>rihi
fam<u>atha</u> ta/muroon**a**

35\. "His plan is to get you out  
Of your land by his sorcery;  
Then what is it ye counsel?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_036.gif)

36. Q<u>a</u>loo arjih waakh<u>a</u>hu wa**i**bAAath fee
almad<u>a</u>-ini <u>ha</u>shireen**a**

36\. They said: "Keep him  
And his brother in suspense  
(For a while), and dispatch  
To the Cities heralds to collect—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_037.gif)

37. Ya/tooka bikulli sa<u>hha</u>rin AAaleem**in**

37\. "And bring up to thee  
All (our) sorcerers well-versed."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_038.gif)

38. FajumiAAa a**l**ssa<u>h</u>aratu limeeq<u>a</u>ti yawmin
maAAloom**in**

38\. So the sorcerers were got  
Together for the appointment  
Of a day well-known,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_039.gif)

39. Waqeela li**l**nn<u>a</u>si hal antum mujtamiAAoon**a**

39\. And the people were told:  
"Are ye (now) assembled?—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_040.gif)

40. LaAAallan<u>a</u> nattabiAAu a**l**ssa<u>h</u>arata in k<u>a</u>noo
humu algh<u>a</u>libeen**a**

40\. "That we may follow  
The sorcerers (in religion)  
If they win?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_041.gif)

41. Falamm<u>a</u> j<u>a</u>a a**l**ssa<u>h</u>aratu q<u>a</u>loo
lifirAAawna a-inna lan<u>a</u> laajran in kunn<u>a</u> na<u>h</u>nu
algh<u>a</u>libeen**a**

41\. So when the sorcerers arrived,  
They said to Pharaoh:  
"Of course—shall we have  
A (suitable) reward  
If we win?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_042.gif)

42. Q<u>a</u>la naAAam wa-innakum i<u>th</u>an lamina almuqarrabeen**a**

42\. He said: "Yea, (and more),—  
For ye shall in that case  
Be (raised to posts)  
Nearest (to my person)."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_043.gif)

43. Q<u>a</u>la lahum moos<u>a</u> alqoo m<u>a</u> antum mulqoon**a**

43\. Moses said to them:  
"Throw ye—that which  
Ye are about to throw!"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_044.gif)

44. Faalqaw <u>h</u>ib<u>a</u>lahum waAAi<u>s</u>iyyahum waq<u>a</u>loo
biAAizzati firAAawna inn<u>a</u> lana<u>h</u>nu algh<u>a</u>liboon**a**

44\. So they threw their ropes  
And their rods, and said:  
"By the might of Pharaoh,  
It is we who will  
Certainly win!"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_045.gif)

45. Faalq<u>a</u> moos<u>a</u> AAa<u>sa</u>hu fa-i<u>tha</u> hiya
talqafu m<u>a</u> ya/fikoon**a**

45\. Then Moses threw his rod,  
When, behold, it straightway  
Swallows up all  
The falsehoods which they fake!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_046.gif)

46. Faolqiya a**l**ssa<u>h</u>aratu s<u>a</u>jideen**a**

46\. When did the sorcerers  
Fall down, prostrate in adoration,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_047.gif)

47. Q<u>a</u>loo <u>a</u>mann<u>a</u> birabbi alAA<u>a</u>lameen**a**

47\. Saying: "We believe  
In the Lord of the Worlds,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_048.gif)

48. Rabbi moos<u>a</u> wah<u>a</u>roon**a**

48\. "The Lord of Moses and Aaron."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_049.gif)

49. Q<u>a</u>la <u>a</u>mantum lahu qabla an <u>ath</u>ana lakum innahu
lakabeerukumu alla<u>th</u>ee AAallamakumu a**l**ssi<u>h</u>ra falasawfa
taAAlamoona laoqa<u>tt</u>iAAanna aydiyakum waarjulakum min
khil<u>a</u>fin walao<u>s</u>allibannakum ajmaAAeen**a**

49\. Said (Pharaoh): "Believe ye  
In Him before I give  
You permission? Surely he  
Is your leader, who has  
Taught you sorcery!  
But soon shall ye know!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_050.gif)

50. Q<u>a</u>loo l<u>a</u> <u>d</u>ayra inn<u>a</u> il<u>a</u>
rabbin<u>a</u> munqaliboon**a**

50\. "Be sure I will cut off  
Your hands and your feet  
On opposite sides, and I  
Will cause you all  
To die on the cross!"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_051.gif)

51. Inn<u>a</u> na<u>t</u>maAAu an yaghfira lan<u>a</u> rabbun<u>a</u>
kha<u>ta</u>y<u>a</u>n<u>a</u> an kunn<u>a</u> awwala almu/mineen**a**

51\. They said: "No matter!  
For us, we shall but  
Return to our Lord!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_052.gif)

52. Waaw<u>h</u>ayn<u>a</u> il<u>a</u> moos<u>a</u> an asri
biAAib<u>a</u>dee innakum muttabaAAoon**a**

52\. "Only, our desire is  
That our Lord will  
Forgive us our faults,  
That we may become  
Foremost among the Believers!"

